<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1287,1381]" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">
Shells of Recent species of 
<taxonomicName box="[508,583,1288,1311]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Hortia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="11" pageNumber="250" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[508,583,1288,1311]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="250">Hortia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to fossil ones, but attain a larger adult size. All Recent species known so far have a non-planktotrophic, bulbous, smooth protoconch rather than the multispiral protoconch of the fossils.
</paragraph>
